title.narrative: Feed the Future Malawi Strengthening Agriculture and Nutrition Extension Services (SANE)

description.narrative: (Malawi): Feed the Future's Strengthening Agricultural and Nutrition Extension (SANE) activity will continue to provide training and technical assistance to extension agents and lead farmers to strengthen the capacity of the Government of Malawi and private sector agribusinesses to deliver agriculture and nutrition extension services. In FY 2019, SANE will prioritize the consolidation of gains made over the past 4 years and share the model with other districts outside geographical focus in the final year of implementation. SANE will focus on: 1) rolling out the AgREACH Extension Helper, an extension service delivery accountability system, and other ICTs to help ensure quality of service delivery; 2) training and coaching of extension agents at various levels to serve as champions for sustainability of impacts and to help roll out methodologies used by SANE beyond the primary zone of influence; 3) training and coaching stakeholder panels at district and sub-district levels in standard operating procedures; and 4) building capacity in participatory extension approaches to help households derive better agricultural and nutritional outcomes. SANE will use organizational capacity assessment tools to evaluate progress made in strengthening capacities of various platforms to determine its primary focus areas. Access to quality extension services is essential for enhancing productivity and nutrition outcomes and thereby contributing to reductions in poverty and stunting. Reduced poverty and stunting will help achieve the Mission's Development Objective 2: Sustainable Livelihoods Increased. SANE will help farming communities hold extension institutions accountable and ensure they are responsive to farmers' needs; strengthening systems for leveraging private sector resources; and helping farmers to capitalize on new technologies. The activity will continue to focus on the 10 FTF districts in central and southern Malawi.. ..
